  "riddle": "1. Seek the streaming giant that began its journey as a mail-order rental service in the year when the world first embraced the internet for leisure — what year was that?\n\n2. What video service, birthed by a fierce competitor known for online shopping, has sported the same logo since a year in the early 2010s?\n\n3. A certain streaming platform hails from a tech leader known for its sleek devices. Discover how many languages this article is translated into — what number do you find?\n\n4. From the answer to clue 3, unveil its digital root; this sums the digits of your answer until a single digit remains.\n\n5. There exists a legacy studio famous for its roaring lion. Dig deep to find out in which year this cinematic institution was established.\n\n6. How many days separate the promising debut of a certain retail house in 1985 from its ultimate closure in 2026?\n\n7. What number emerges when you take the result from clue 6 and reverse its digits? \n\n8. Journey to the town where the streaming titans find their roots. How many languages can you discover listed in that article?\n\n9. Seek the height above sea level of that very town — what figure do you uncover?\n\n10. Count the nearby stadiums that surround this charming locale — how many can you find?\n\n11. Take the elevation from clue 9 and combine it with the stadium count from clue 10 by calculating the absolute difference (110 - 20). \n\n12. Now, revisit the altitude of this bustling town — what is its elevation again?\n\n13. Compute the final value by finding the absolute difference between the results of clue 3 and clue 6, then taking the result modulo 10: abs(clue 3 - clue 6) % 10. \n\nThis last computation should yield your final answer, a single digit ranging from 0 to 9.",
